title: Crowell, Bulldogs Win First Home Sweep
text:
Crowell, Bulldogs Win First Home Sweep 
By Norman Seawright III October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 10:56 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- To round out the home and Western Collegiate Hockey Association (WCHA) opener, the University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) women's hockey team swept Minnesota State University-Mankato (MSU). 
Maddie Rooney had fourteen saves in goal for UMD, while four goals for the Bulldogs led to a 4-0 shutout, moving the team to a 4-4 record, and earning the first home sweep for Head Coach Maura Crowell.
